By Abiemwense Moru Abuja – President Muhammadu Buhari has commended the two chambers of the National Assembly for the expeditious attention they accorded the new minimum wage bill. The President’s Senior Special Assistants on National Assembly
Matters, Senator Ita Enang and Hon. Umar El-Yakub, gave the commendation
in a chat with journalists at the Assembly complex on Thursday. El-Yakub, who recently took over from Hon. Abdulrahman Kawu Sumaila
as SSA (House of Representatives) to the President, said Buhari was
delighted with the manner both chambers commenced prompt consideration
of the bill. According to him, the President commends the leadership and members
of the National Assembly for the expeditious reading of the minimum wage
bill. “It shows the lawmakers are ready to work with President Buhari; and
it is also a show of concern for the wellbeing of Nigerians,” he said. The new SSA promised to work with the leadership of both chambers and
ensure a cordial relationship between the legislature and the
executive. Also, Enang reiterated that the action of the lawmakers was a “demonstration of faith in the government of President Muhammadu Buhari by the lawmakers.”  (NAN)